tip.text: Cool neighborhood with plenty of restaurants, galleries, parks, boutiques. A quick and worthwhile walk from Tower Bridge and the Shard.
Excellent flat whites. Funny and friendly staff. Cozy couches and great hip vibe. Across from White Cube in trendy Bermondsey.
Beautiful property w. contemporary and cozy rooms. Lovely bar and great breakfast from Jamie's Italian downstairs. Professional and helpful staff. 5 min. walk to Bermondsey, London Tower Bridge Tube.
North Side Social gets all the hype, but Java Shack is just a good, local, community-oriented coffee shop. Great cold brew (and nitro!), fun espresso drinks, tasty local pastries, and a sunny patio.
You cannot go wrong here! Love the unusual savory pies (BBQ pork, sausage-tomato-fennel), quiche (spinach/goat cheese), and Baltimore Bomb. They have a liquor license and do a great Irish coffee!

formattedAddress: 1339 H St NE (at Linden Ct. NE)

tip.text: Gorgeous, tasty macarons in a modern space w. Intelligentsia coffee! Loved blood orange & blueberry cheesecake. Staff needs more training - gave me 12 oz. coffee concentrate instead of iced coffee.
Great little counter service + salad bar spot in Park Place II. Love the falafel and breakfast sandwiches. Staff will quickly learn your name and preferences. Huge portions and affordable.

Fantastic addition to the Tysons dining scene. Slick decor and mid-priced for the area. Loved the curried cauliflower, brussels sprouts with nam prik, dolsot bibimbap (rice bowls), & pork belly ramen.
Great beer store with an extensive selection of local brews and tons of seasonal selections from around the country. Several taps feature Virginia beers and growlers (plus tasting!) are available.

tip.text: Outstanding oyster happy hour! Cocktails are super creative and other sides - like the fries - are fresh and delicious. Service a little scatterbrained but well-meaning.
